19/03/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- A makeshift bomb exploded early Friday (March 19th) outside the office of a far-right group in Athens.
The blast caused damage but no injuries.
The office of Chryssi Avghi (Golden Dawn) is on the fifth floor of a building near Omonia Square.
Police evacuated the building after a caller phoned a warning into the daily newspaper Eleftherotypia.
(Reuters, CNN, ANA-MPA - 19/03/10)
